body:
I think you've confused package name with import path.

When importing a package, the string used is the import
path, and when using the imported package, the identifier
used is the package name. In general, they can be totally
unrelated.

For example, it's possible to import "abc/def/v1" and the
package name be def.

The import path doesn't have to be a Go identifier, so
removing the quotes will make the syntax more complicated
and irregular.
